      h2.row-space-6.text-center Privacy Policy
      p.introduction
        | Huber. Inc. (the “Company”) hereby stipulates as follows this Privacy Policy (this “Policy”) to appropriately manage User Information including personal information of customers of services (“Services”) provided by the Company.
      dl
        dt.row-space-1.row-space-top-3
          span.num-ol
            | 1.
          span
            | User Information to be collected and collection method
        dd
          p
            | “User Information” in this Policy means information related to customer identification, a customer’s action history on communication services, and other information related to customers or the customers terminals generated or stored on customers smartphones, personal computers, or other terminals that the Company collects pursuant to this Policy.
            br
            | User Information the Company will collect through the Services include the following in accordance with the collection method.
          p.num-wrapper
            span.num
              | (1)
            span
              | Information provided by the customer
          p.inside
            | Information that a customer will provide to use the Services is as follows:
          ul.inside
            li Name
            li Address
            li Telephone number
            li Email address
            li Date of birth
            li Age
            li Gender
            li Photograph (one with content and in a form separately designated by the Company; hereinafter the same in this Policy)
            li Credit card information
            li Other information inputted by the customer on an input form stipulated by the Company
        dd
          p.num-wrapper
            span.num
              | (2)
            span
              | Information that, when a customer permits linkage with other services in using the Services, is provided by such other services
          p.inside
            | If when using the Services, a customer permits linkage with social network services and other external services, the Company may collect information provided by external services with which linkage has been permitted. Such information includes the following:
          ul.inside
            li IDs and other identification information that a customer uses on such external services
            li Other information that a customer permits on the privacy settings of such external services disclosure to linkage partners
        dd
          p.num-wrapper
            span.num
              | (3)
            span
              | Information the Company collects through the customer’s use of the Services
          p.inside
            | The Company may collect access conditions and other information related to the method of using the Services. Such information includes the following:
          ul.inside
            li IDs unique to contractual parties or terminals (such as IDs generated by OS (Android ID), owner terminal identification number (UDID), subscriber identity number (IMSI), and MAC address)
            li Log information
            li Identification information generated by the use of cookie technology
            li Location information

        dt.row-space-1.row-space-top-3
          span.num-ol
            | 2.
          span
            | Purposes of use
        dd
          p.num-wrapper
            span.num
              | (1)
            span
              | User Information will be used for the provision of the Services as stipulated in Paragraph (2) of this Article 2, and may also be used for other purposes as stipulated in Paragraph (3) of this Article 2.
        dd
          p.num-wrapper
            span.num
              | (2)
            span
              | The specific purposes of use of User Information related to the provision of the Services are as follows:
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ①
            span
              | To accept registration, confirm identification, and calculate use fees;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ②
            span
              | In a case where a customer uses the Services to provide or display the customer’s products or services (“Provide etc.”), to disclose to viewers of the Services the customer’s User Information that is necessary to identify products and services, and to appropriately describe the products and services;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ③
            span
              | In a case where the customer uses the Services to request provision of products or services for which a third party other than the Company is the seller or host, to disclose to the provider or host of such products or services the customer’s User Information that is necessary for the provision of such products or services, and to appropriately provide such products or services to the customer;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ④
            span
              | To maintain and protect the Services, improve the accuracy of the recommendation function related to the Services, and otherwise enhance the quality of the Services;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ⑤
            span
              | To provide explanations and respond to inquiries concerning the Services;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ⑥
            span
              | To send information regarding after-care services related to the Services, and new products and services;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ⑦
            span
              | To deal with conduct that violates the Company’s rules, policies and the like (“Rules etc.”) relating to the Services;
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ⑧
            span
              | To give notice of any changes to Rules etc. relating to the Services; and
          p.num-wrapper-inside
            span.num-inside
              | ⑨
            span
              | For purposes of use ancillary to the foregoing purposes of use.
          dd
            p.num-wrapper
              span.num
                | (3)
              span
                | Purposes of use other than those set forth in the above Paragraph (2) of this Article 2 are as follows:
            p.num-wrapper-inside
              span.num-inside
                | ①
              span
                | To create statistical data processed in a format that cannot identify individuals in relation to the Company’s services;
                br
                | (Type of User Information that will be handled)
            ul.inside
              li
                | IDs unique to contractual parties or terminals
              li
                | Age
              li
                | Gender
              li
                | Residential area
              li
                | Information on messages between hosts and guests
              li
                | Information regarding screen transitions within pages
              li
                | Information on favorite tours
              li
                | All hosts and guests review information
              li
                | Settlement amounts and number of settlements
              li
                | Other log information
              li
                | Other identification information generated by the use of cookie technology
              li
                | Location information
            p.num-wrapper-inside
              span.num-inside
                | ②
              span
                | To improve the accuracy of the recommendation function related to the Services, and to otherwise distribute or display advertisements of the Company or third parties
                br
                | (Type of User Information that will be handled)
            ul.inside
              li
                | IDs unique to contractual parties or terminals
              li
                | Age
              li
